description: The ages long war between the Vampire and Werewolf Nations has finally ended. During a bloody climactic battle, opposing leaders Lord Drakken and Armand Waering were both slain, leaving behind a new and younger generation of supernaturals to gorge a tenuous truce. However the cost of creating this peace was high for the WetWorks team. Dozer and Claymore were killed in action, leaving the squad with only five of its original members. In addition, their one trusted friend from the intelligence organization known as International Operations, Benjamin Santini, was forced to storm the Oval Office and pull a gun on the President of the United States to prevent him from nuking the city of Phoenix. As a result, the stage has been set for an all-new direction for this slite military combat team...
name: Sacraments Of Damnation, Part 4

description:
With the ages long war between the Vampire and Werewolf Nations finally over, the surviving WetWorks teamp members hoped to be able to start their lives anew. Unfortunately, they found themselves summoned instead to the headquarters of International Operations, where the mysterious Dominique Faust asked these former Team 7 soldiers to once again become I.O.'s official strike team. 
Not trusting I.O. to determine their missions, the team rejected her offer. In retaliation, Dominique had WetWorks arrested on charges of treason and desertion, and placed them in a hi-tech prison. In the end, however, it turned out that Dane had a plan all along. WetWorks easily escaped their confinement, and proved to Dominique just how powerful and elusive they couls be. The team then returned to her office and agreed to work for I.O.... but only on their terms!
name: Maximum Security

description:
The WetWorks team agreed, so long as they could control the selection of their mission, to serve as I.O.'s official strike team. With this deal, they then traveled to Los Angeles to investigate a new alliance between global terrorist St. Crispin and Lara Hawthorne, the head of the multi-national Avalon Corporation. Soon after their arrival, Jester and Grail found themselves fighting a super-powered pair of mercenaries named Search and Destroy, while across town, Dane and Mother One learned that St. Crispin and Hawthorne were actually plotting to start a race war. 
Perched above a marina, Pilgrim received orders to simply sniper and eliminate the pair of evildoers. However, just as she took aim, a silver blade flew forth striking her weapon and ruining her shot. Looking up, she found herself facing the hero Loner, who now wanted of his own answered!
name: Diversionary Tactics, Part 1

description: Teamed with Loner, WetWorks raced the clock to locate bombs planted across the city. Unfortunately, while each explosive was ultimately stopped, the heroic effort came at an extremely high cost: for Dane was captured by St. Crispin and Hawthorne, who then stole his symbiotes forcibly from his body !
name: Diversionary Tactics, Part 2

description:
During a recent battle against the global terrorist St. Crispin and the evil Lara Hawthorne, head of the powerful Avalon Corporation, Dane was not only captured but had his golden synbiote forcibly stripped from his body. Hoping to resecure it, the WetWorks team tracked the evil duo to Suenos Perdidos, a capital city in South America, and a secret laboratory hidden beneath the presidential palace. Unfortunately, as the heroes attacked, Grail was forced to fight an energy being known as E=MC2, and their subsequent struggle caused an explosion that totally destroyed the palace. Admist the ruins, Dane was no longer able to sense his symbiote, and concluded that ir must have been totally destroyed in the conflict. So he ordered the team to move out... 
 However, unbeknownst to them all, two further events transpired. First, Dane's symbiote wasn't destroyed. During the palace explosion, Hawthorne actually fell into the glass cas that was housing it and now possesses it on her own body! And secondly, the global guardians known as StormWatch arrived thereafter to investigate the carnage, only to leanr from a dying St. Crispin that WetWorks was responsible!
name: Diversionary Tactics, Part 3

description:
Given their violations of international law, Weatherman Jackson King subsequently ordered the capture of WetWorks, with Grail, Jester and Mother One the first to fall at the hands of StormWatch members Winter and Flint.

However, in retaliation Dane and Pilgrim kidnapped StormWatch teammates Fahrenheit and Hellstrike. Dane then teleported himself up onto Skywatch, setting the stage for a tumultuous showdown...
name: Drawn Swords, Part 1

description:
The United Nations superteam StormWatch arrived in South America to investigate and learned of WetWorks involvement from a dying St. Crispin in the destruction of a building. As a result, Weatherman Jackson King ordered their capture, with Grail, Jester and Mother One being the forst to fall. This prompted Dane and Pilgrim to kidnap two StormWatch teammates in retaliation, to hols as their own bargaining chips. They then teleported up on to SkyWatch, were they fought against Weatherman King and his crew, and ultimately succeeded in rescuing their teammates. 
However, on their return to Earth, WetWorks was shocked to learn from Alicia Turner, their friend and an I.O. agent, that Mother One, who had been sent ahead due to her injuries, had mysteriously chosen to wander off without waiting for the rest of the team. Confused by this, Dane nonetheless vouched for Turner's word and trustworthness, while Grail refused to believe the story and stormed off. 
Twelve hours later, in a secret lab hidden beneath a mountain in West Virginia, the supposedly trustworthy Alicia Turner ominously worked on an unconscious Mother One, exposing her to a mysterious glowing box and an ominous, disembodied voice. A few moments later, Mother One awoke, but no longer remembered who she was! Worse, she now called herself Tanager, and screamed that she wanted to see Jackson Dane dead!
name: Drawn Swords, Part 2

description:
A short while later the last issue, WetWOrks received word that Mother One had been kidnapped and that as her ransom, Dan now needed to reassemble his surviving teammates from the original Team 7. Though rebuffed by Marc Slayton (aka Backlash), Dane did manage to capture John Lynch. WetWorks then boardeda robot plane with him in tow as instructed, which took off for an unknown site... 
Meanwhile, in New York City, Cole Cash (aka the Grifter), found himself attacked by a clearly evil Alicia Turner, who was also now calling herself Tanager. Giving chase on his bullet bike motorcycle, Grifter tailed her to the Castkill mountains and the aforementioned underground lab. There, ha was psychically assaulted, and his body was possessed by the former disembodied voice. 
Finally, WetWorks found themselves confronting their own new surprise as on board the plane, Mother One suddenly appeared from out the cockpit and declared that she no longer needed any of them... and that the plane could now be destroyed!
name: Flashback, Part 1

description: Last issue of WetWorks Volume 1
name: Flashback, Part 2

description:
Guest-written by Eisner Award winner J.M. DeMatteis!
Can a cyborg die? That's the question Dane has to confront when Mother-One is suddenly gripped by a mysterious - and deadly - illness. Ab-Death holds the key to the mystery...but it will take an extraordinary journey into Deadworld to find the answers.
name: A Short Walk to Eternity, Part 1: Dead Again

description: Ab-Death, determined to bring Mother One back from the Deadworld before her soul is beyond his reach, risks his own soul and, in the process, learns a terrible truth about who and what he truly is.
name: A Short Walk to Eternity Part 2: Golden Slumbers

description: The vampire known as Red comes clean to Dane about her former life as an assassin, as well as her reason for joining the Wetworks team.
name: Idyll

description: The original Wetworks team is back together and, augmented by new members such as Ab-Death and Ashe, stronger than ever. But even that looks like it might not be enough, as the enhanced Night Tribes take over eastern Europe.
name: Unholy War Part One

description: As the Wetworks team tries to stem the tide and prevent the vampire nation from overrunning Europe, Red and Dane discover there’s a new heir to King Savoy’s throne…an heir who’s being tutored by Ab-Death.
name: Unholy War Part Two

description: Ever wonder why they call her Voodoo? Priscilla is about to find out when she meets a Daemonite Shaman prepared to teach her exactly why their alien race is the most feared and hated in all the Omniverse! (Hint: It has surprisingly little to do with their fangs, talons and impenetrable armored hides!) Plus, more about Dr. Jeremy Stone ‹ now the massive Maul ‹ and his efforts to help Priscilla rid herself of her alien genetic heritage... and the awesome price he and Priscilla both must pay in the process. Does that sound like a lot for one issue? Welcome to the world of the all-new, all-different Wildcats... now buckle in and enjoy the trip!
name: Second Skin

description: The dramatic events bridging the gap between WILDC.A.T.S Volume 1 and the exciting WILDCATS Volume 2 are finally revealed! What caused the 'Cats to split apart? Where are Zealot and Warblade? Venture into the not-too-distant past as a routine WildC.A.T.s mission to Ireland turns into an unforgettable nightmare. Grifter, Zealot, Warblade, Voodoo, and Spartan find themselves in a gruesome battle they cannot win ‹ a battle that tests their friendship, loyalty and faith in one another as their survival hangs in the balance.
name: Firefight

description: A special issue featuring art by THE AUTHORITY's Bryan Hitch and Paul Neary! What begins in a seedy L.A. liquor store turns into an exciting adventure in the newest issue of WILDCATS. When a nearby street gang lingers chooses the wrong night to cause trouble, they run afoul of a dangerous figure lurking in the shadows. Will this mysterious guest star become the newest member of the 'Cats?
name: Coda-fied

description: Since Zealot's death, Grifter and the nefarious Kenyan have become fierce enemies. Now, thanks to Noir's mysterious — and somewhat illegal — connections, the 'Cats have finally gotten a serious lead on this manipulative villain. The stalking ground is New York City. Close your eyes and cover your ears, because if one of the Wildcats catches Kenyan, it won't be pretty. Let the chase begin!
name: The Chase

description:
The series goes monthly with the debut of its new creative team!

An exciting new era for the Wildcats dawns in February's WILDCATS Volume 2 #8 as the book goes monthly, with a new writer-artist team set to amp up the tension and intrigue! Travis Charest stays on board as cover artist, while, between the covers, new writer Joe Casey (X-Men: Children of the Atom, MR. MAJESTIC) is joined by incredibly versatile artist Sean Phillips (HELLBLAZER, Webspinners: Tales of Spider-Man, LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES)! And the first issue features a stunning variant cover by Jim Lee and Scott Williams! (This cover will interlock with the Lee/Williams variant offered for GEN13 #50.)

Writer Joe Casey's long-term plans for the 'Cats include the return of Ladytron (who he recently featured in MR. MAJESTIC #3) as part of the regular cast, along with plans for increased roles for Void and another familiar character whose identity will shock WILDCATS readers. In WILDCATS Volume 2 #8, part 1 of a bold 3-part story, Lord Emp has disappeared! Grifter is convinced that Kenyan is somehow involved, but is the unthinkable true? Has Emp turned traitor? What dark secrets will Cole Cash uncover during his investigation? The answers — and the nonstop action — start coming monthly with WILDCATS Volume 2 #8!
name: Heavenly Shades

description: The new creative team of writer Joe Casey and artist Sean Phillips hits new heights with a wild Las Vegas adventure! The Wildcats hit Vegas as the screws tighten on Emp and Kenyan! The search for all the answers continues as more of Kenyan's secrets are revealed. While Emp gambles on his future as a High Lord of Eternal Light, the Wildcats find themselves unexpectedly caught up in a casino heist masterminded by a former supervillain.
name: Set My Soul on Fire

description: The first storyline from the creative team of writer Joe Casey and artist Sean Phillips concludes as the final fates of both Lord Emp and the immortal villain, Kenyan, are revealed! Their secret history finally out in the open, the unexpected ending to this century-long conflict will shock new and longtime readers alike, with the WILDCATS cast changing dramatically as a result.
name: Deal of the Century

description:
First apperence of Mike Danger

This comic also has some of the first work for comics by Steve Ditko.

This issue features the epic matchup Seth VS Akuma, plus appearances by Sakura, Dan, C.Viper, Abel, El Fuerte, and more! Also, the issue will feature the first in-story appearance of one of the all-new characters for Super Street Fighter IV(heck, they game won’t even be out until Spring 2010!). So don’t miss it!

It’s bad girl VS school girl as Crimsom Viper makes Sakura her latest target! How does Sakura fit into the S.I.N. organization’s plan.. and why would they want Dan Hibiki as well? The answers could be DARKER than anyone suspects!

Nothing less than the fate of the free world is at stake as Sgt. Nick Fury leads the Howling Commandos on their most dangerous mission ever! SHOTGUN OPERA sets the stage for the harrowing events of Jeph Loeb and Tim Sale's best-selling CAPTAIN AMERICA: WHITE. After parachuting deep into enemy-held Yugoslavia, Fury, Dum Dum, Izzy, Reb, Gabe, and Pinky Pinkerton need every bullet and grenade in the Allied armory as they are chased by Tiger tanks, strafed by screaming Stukas, betrayed by beautiful babes, and forced into gladiatorial combat against Baron Strucker's diabolical war machine: PANZER MAX! Brought to you by the team of Jesse Alexander (HEROES, LOST, ALIAS) and John Paul Leon (EARTH X), HOWLING COMMANDOES is a must-have for all Fury Fans, Cap Completists, and anyone who likes war comics that take no prisoners, show no mercy, and cry havoc! WA-HOO!
name: Shotgun Opera!

description: A follow up sequel to the movie and graphic novel sensation, "Road to Perdition."
name: Oasis

description: The second of three untold tales from the graphic novel and Oscar-winning movie! Where will gangster Michael O'Sullivan - on the run with his young son - seek sanctuary from the vicious bounty hunters on his trail?
name: Sanctuary

description: The hard-boiled finale to the 3-volume prequel of untold tales relating to the graphic novel and Oscar-winning movie ROAD TO PERDITION! Michael O'Sullivan, on the run from the crime syndicate that destroyed his own family, finds himself in Kansas City with his young son as their run of bank robberies nears its end. Now he's headed for a showdown with the murderous kingpin's heir whose history - and destiny - is completely entangled with his own!
name: Detour

description: As payment for killing Selma Rosencrantz, Johnny Dynamite leaves Freddie Faust for dead in the Las Vegas desert. But Faust gets a helping hand from a particular pal in Hades, and That Old Black Magic can work wonders on even a dead man! He formulates his plan for revenge, complete with an army of zombie henchmen, and things start looking explosive for Johnny Dynamite!

Johnny Dynamite continues his vendetta against Freddie Faust, the devil-dealing gangster. They're looking to kill each other, and while Johnny has right on his side, Faust has an army of zombies. All hell is breaking loose (literally) leading Johnny to the "Underworld," the thrilling conclusion to the fast-paced crime-horror thriller.

1. The Five Doomed Men

2. The Wisdom of Great Owl

3. The Traitor
name: The Five Doomed Men ; The Widom of great Owl ; The Traitor

1. Bye-Bye, Money Bin (Uncle Scrooge, Donald Duck, Huey, Dewey, and Louie, Beagle Boys / written by Vic Lockman : reprinted in: Uncle Scrooge #167, Walt Disney's Uncle Scrooge #290)

description: All good things must eventually end. Sure, our universe had some great times, but all shows must close, and the Fantastic Four are summoned to the Ends of Time to help one of the show's brightest stars pack up for the long sleep until the next universe is born. That's right: Galactus has survived one Big Bang, and is making plans to pull off the same trick! But what does a guy like Galactus pack for this journey, and why does he need the help of the Fantastic Four? Plus, artist Colleen Coover brings you Sue Storm's essay, "The Importance of Being Invisible!"
name: Moving Day

description: It's Paris in the springtime! Our 3-part revue of The Spirit's finest female foils concludes with the woman who puts the femme in femme fatale, the toast of Montmartre: Plaster of Paris! Where this beauty goes, murder follows en suite!
name: Plastered In Paris

description: The issue in which Johnny Dynamite losses an eye.

Note

The patch is on the left eye on the cover here, before and there after it is over the right eye.
Last issue published by Comics Media, the title next shows up from Charlton.

description: The green-finned cop known as Savage Dragon was busy fighting a bunch of ruthless evildoers who called themselves Johnny Redbeard’s Nixxed Men (a barely disguised jab at John Byrne’s Next Men). Unfortunately for all concerned, the action was observed over in the Megahero Universe by the Megatropolis Quartet. Exercising their limited intellects, they concluded that the alternate universe known as Earth-Image had been attacked by green-finned aliens. Since the colorfully clad Nixxed Men were being beaten up so badly, they decide to send Megaton Man in to rescue them. The rest, as they say, was chaos.
name: Special Edition

description: The war begins! The Greeks send envoys to the Trojans to demand the return of Helen, but they are rebuffed. The Greeks land at Troy, led by Achilles, and drive the Trojans back. But Achilles rushes into the city alone and is slain by an arrow shot by Paris. This war, it seems, will never end.
name: Part Two

volume.name: The Amazing Spider-Man 30th Anniversary Poster Magazine

description:
It's One Year Later…and a dying Vandal Savage has crash-landed on Earth after the worst twelve months of his life. His last order of business? Revenge on Green Lantern!

Don't miss the Part 1 of a 4-part story written by Stuart Moore (FIRESTORM) with art by Paul Gulacy & Jimmy Palmiotti (CATWOMAN, YEAR ONE: BATMAN/RA'S AL GHUL)!
name: The Fall & Rise of Vandal Savage, Part One

description: Vandal Savage sets in motion his plan to destroy Alan Scott. His scheme might get a bit more complicated when an unexpected friend from the past arrives to help the Golden Age Green Lantern!
name: The Fall & Rise of Vandal Savage, Part Two

story_arc_credits.name: The Fall & Rise of Vandal Savage

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: The Fall & Rise of Vandal Savage

description: As the issue begins, Donatello's dreams are being disturbed by a disembodied voice, questioning the distressed Turtle about how he can sleep while the Voice's granddaughter is struggling. On the following page we find ourselves inside of Don's dream, where he sits as a giant upon a mountain in the forest. By the mammoth Turtle's side is an equally gigantic Native American chief, who floats cross-legged in the sky.
name: Dreams of Stone

description: Desperation sets in as Vandal Savage moves closer to death's door...and Alan Scott continues to avoid his wrath! But Savage's latest scheme just might hit the Golden Age Green Lantern too close to home.
name: The Fall & Rise of Vandal Savage, Part Three
